   "source": [
    "## Linear Regression\n",
    "This notebook trains a linear regression model to determine which non-embedding features are most strongly associated with the derived engagement score."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ef10962c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Steps outlined\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Load pre-built feature matrices (cols 768–796, excluding text embeddings)\n",
    "2. Recompute continuous `engagement_score` from raw parquet via row indices\n",
    "3. Apply min-max scaling uniformly across all 29 non-embedding features\n",
    "4. Train `LinearRegression` and evaluate on val/test (MSE, R²)\n",
    "5. Visualize coefficient importance bar chart and feature correlation heatmap"
   ]
  },
